# Roles

## Personal User (v1 — implemented)

Version 1 is designed for personal use. A signed-in user can:

- Create and delete decks
- Rename deck and lesson titles (pencil icon on deck detail)
- Create and delete lessons
- **Practice** endlessly (primary mode on app open)
- **Daily Review** for spaced repetition when cards are due
- Track progress on the dashboard
- Import learning content (JSON — upload or paste, then confirm)
- Search decks, lessons, and cards
- Configure theme and sign out

**Not in v1:** export, statistics charts, card edit UI on deck page, tags UI, deck description/color edit UI.

---

## Admin (future)

Initially, the admin is the application owner. Not implemented in v1.

Possible future capabilities:

- Manage application settings
- Import sample content for all users
- Maintain default decks
- Role-based access

Possible future roles (out of v1 scope):

- Creator
- Moderator
- Public Deck Publisher

