# Content Import (v1 — implemented)

JSON import is supported via Settings → Import Deck.

- File upload (`.json`, `.txt`) or paste — click **Import JSON** to confirm (upload alone does not import)
- Creates deck, lessons, cards, tags, and initial scheduling state
- Large decks imported in batches per lesson
- Generic format works for any subject

**Not in v1:** CSV, Excel, Markdown, PDF, `.revia` package export/import.

---

# JSON Structure

```json
{
  "deck": {
    "title": "Kannada Basics",
    "description": "Beginner vocabulary and phrases",
    "tags": ["language", "beginner"]
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "title": "Greetings",
      "description": "Basic greetings",
      "cards": [
        {
          "front": "ನಮಸ್ಕಾರ (namaskara)",
          "back": "Hello / Greetings",
          "pronunciation": "namaskara",
          "example": "ನಮಸ್ಕಾರ, ಹೇಗಿದ್ದೀರ?",
          "notes": "Formal greeting",
          "tags": ["greeting", "beginner"]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

**Required:** deck title, lesson title, card front, card back. All other fields optional.

